text: Jaouad Achab (born August 20, 1992) is a taekwondo practitioner from Belgium. He won the gold medal at the 2014 European Championships Men's 63 kg, and at the 2015 World Championships, becoming Belgium's first World Taekwondo champion. In 2019, he won one of the bronze medals in the men's bantamweight event at the 2019 World Taekwondo Championships in Manchester, United Kingdom. == References == Category:Belgian male taekwondo practitioners Category:1992 births Category:Living people Category:Taekwondo practitioners at the 2015 European Games Category:European Games competitors for Belgium Category:Olympic taekwondo practitioners of Belgium Category:Taekwondo practitioners at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Universiade medalists in taekwondo Category:Universiade gold medalists for Belgium Category:European Taekwondo Championships medalists Category:World Taekwondo Championships medalists Category:Medalists at the 2015 Summer Universiade
